==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Psalmist
<hw>Psalm"ist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>psalmista</ets>, Gr. <?/: cf. F. <ets>psalmiste</ets>. See
<er>Psalm</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A writer or composer of sacred
songs; -- a title particularly applied to David and the other authors of
the Scriptural psalms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>A clerk, precentor, singer,
or leader of music, in the church.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Psalmistry</ent>⟦br⟧
